How to find us in London:
By Tube
The nearest tube station is Green Park, on the Piccadilly, Victoria and Jubilee Lines. Take the exit for Buckingham Palace and walk east along Piccadilly, past the Ritz Hotel. Charlemagne Capital is on the corner of Piccadilly and St James’s Street.
By car
The nearest car park is in Arlington Street. A Congestion Charge is payable during normal business hours.
By bus
Piccadilly is served by a number of bus routes, including 8, 9, 14, 19, 22 and 38. Eastbound buses stop outside the Royal Academy, westbound buses opposite Bond Street; from where it is a short walk to Charlemagne Capital.
 
 
 







